Football pundits accuse foreign tacticians of using top teams to better their CVs  High turnover of coaches marks Covid-19 ravaged Premier League season Football was one of the sports that was heavily affected this year by the deadly coronavirus. 

Three days after the first case of Covid-19 was reported in the country on March 12, the government halted all sporting activities to help combat the spread of the virus. 

In April, Football Kenya Federation (FKF) President Nick Mwendwa, in a tweet, cancelled the 2019/20 Kenyan Premier League (KPL) season and declared Gor Mahia the champions. An average of 23 league games had been played. 



