Football Kenya Federation President Nick Mwendwa addresses a press conference at Safari Park Hotel on November 26, 2020 during the unveiling of StarTimes as official broadcast sponsors of FKF Premier League.
Photo credit: Sila Kiplagat | Nation Media Group

 

A number of coaches in the KPL found the going rough, and were fired over poor performance. Some foreign coaches tendered their resignation, some because of dire straits but others quit under a cloud of suspicion. 

Football pundits think foreigners have been using Kenyan teams, mainly 19-time league champions and their sworn rivals, AFC Leopards to better their curriculum vitae before looking for jobs in other top clubs on the African continent. 



