Gor, Wazito, Leopards, Sofapaka, Bandari and Nzoia Sugar are some of the KPL sides which hired and fired coaches at will. 

Of all the top-flight clubs, Wazito who are into their second season in the top flight, had the highest turnover of coaches last season. 

The club that is currently coached by former Harambee Stars tactician, Francis Kimanzi, dismissed coaches six times. They are Fred Ambani, British coach Stewart Hall, Harambee Stars Under-20 coach Stanley Okumbi, Fred Ouna, youthful tactician Hamisi Abdalla and Egyptian-American Melis Medo. 

Players axed 

The axe not only fell on the tacticians but also on the players who were deemed surplus the squad. 

Among the players shown the door in July controversially included Victor Ndinya, Teddy Osok, Derrick Otanga, goalkeeper Steve Njung’e, Kevin Omondi, Augustine Otu, Piscas Kirenge, Issioffu Bourahana and Paul Acquah. 



