On March 9, Bungoma-based Nzoia Sugar sacked coach Collins “Korea” Omondi due to a string of poor results in the league. 

Nzoia President Evans Kadenge said the decision was taken after the team threw away a 2-0 lead to lose 3-2 to Kakamega Homeboyz at Bukhungu Stadium. He was replaced by Sylvester Mulukurwa and goal keeper trainer Peter Mwaura. 

